<tr><td><strong>Triglycerides</strong></td><td>Below 150 mg/dL</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>Fasting Blood Sugar</strong></td><td>Below 100 mg/dL</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<div class="alert alert-warning mt-4 p-4 shadow-sm" style="border-left: 5px solid #ff9800;">
<h4 class="alert-heading"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>Warning Signs of a Heart Attack</h4>
<p class="mb-0">Never ignore your body. Symptoms can include intense chest pressure, tightness or pain, shortness of breath, pain radiating down the left arm, jaw, or neck, sudden cold sweats, unexplained nausea, and profound fatigue. <strong>Call emergency services immediately if you or someone else experiences these symptoms.</strong> Time is muscle; the faster you get treatment, the more heart tissue can be saved.</p>
</div>

<h2>Conclusion: Your Heart, Your Responsibility</h2>
<p>Your heart deserves the utmost care and attention. Transitioning to a heart-healthy lifestyle does not have to happen overnight. Begin by making small, sustainable changes: swap out a sugary drink for water, take a 15-minute walk after dinner, or schedule a comprehensive check-up with your doctor.</p>
<p>At Sankalp Hospital, our dedicated cardiology department is equipped with state-of-the-art diagnostic tools to assess your cardiovascular risk. From routine EKGs and echocardiograms to advanced stress testing and personalized prevention plans, our team of experts is here to partner with you in achieving lifelong heart health.</p>
